history.content: This is a reasonable workload. However, since you said you are doing data science and business, I would suggest stat 140 instead of 134

How doable is this? I'm an intended cs sophomore having taken 61ab, math 1ab, and currently in 61c and ee 16a. What are the problem sets in ee16b, stat 134, and math 53 like in terms of hours? It takes me about 6-8 hours for the ee16a problem sets just as a measure and I understand the concepts pretty well. 

My intention was that 134 would prep me for the stats portion of cs 70(while covering topics in EE 126). I eventually want to take CS 189, so I want to follow the EE 126, 127, 189 path to get the most of 189. I also want to take the core SWE classes: CS 170, 162, 186, and possibly 161 and 168 and 188. Would 53 help in any of these upper div classes?

Math 53 would is a class that's a prereq for a good amount of upper div classes and in case I don't end up declaring(I need an A- in cs 70), I'll end up doing Data Science with Emphasis on Business Analytics.
history.subject: Math 53 + Stat 134 + EE 16B + 3-unit Breadth
